<TEXT>
national assembly candidate 
luis mejia miranda on monday ridiculed reports he was involved in 
misusing us aid money can you imagine that if i had 2 
million i would still be in this country he asked 
president jose napoleon duartes son denied he was trying to 
protect mejia a fellow christian democrat who was reported under 
investigation in the case 
i deny any tie because i am not protecting him and because i 
am against corruption said alejandro duarte candidate for mayor 
of san salvador in the march 20 elections 
the new york times said sunday that mejia is being investigated 
for allegedly misusing up to 2 million of us aid 
it said the money was part of a 10 million program to assist 
warravaged areas and help win the support of salvadorans in the 
war against leftist rebels 
the newspaper quoted unidentified salvadoran and us officials 
as saying it could be the largest case of theft of us aid money 
during the administration of president duarte elected in may 1984 
for a fiveyear term 
in an interview with local newspapers mejia said that news 
about alleged misuse of funds surprises me because it is totally 
false 
rodolfo castillo claramount duartes vice president and 
secretarygeneral of the governing christian democratic party said 
the article was full of vagueness and imprecisions with the 
political intention of damaging the party 
he said it was written within a strategic conception of the 
ultraright of the country 
he also read a communique saying the party backed alejandro 
duarte as an absolutely honorable capable and honest man 
referring to allegations against mejia the communique said we 
abstain from making a value judgment because we do not know if 
there is evidence 
alejandro duarte denied being an associate of mejia and said he 
had urged mejia to cooperate with any investigation 
it is vital that the truth be arrived at he told reporters 
if he mejia is clean he does not have to be afraid if he 
feels he is outside of the accusations then he should submit 
himself to any investigation 
all this is a dirty political game and i feel indignant for 
having been involved alejandro duarte said 
asked about his relationship with mejia he replied i have no 
personal friendship with him i know him like the majority of the 
members of the party 
the new york times said mejia resigned three months ago as 
director of the national commission for the restoration of areas 
but president duarte agreed to allow him to become a party 
candidate for the national assembly on the recommendation of 
alejandro duarte 
a us embassy source speaking on condition of anonymity said 
these allegations are being studied 
at this time the inspector general of aid the us agency for 
international development has made no determination of bad use of 
funds in this program the source said however other recent 
studies have identified certain aspects of financial control and 
management of conara the restoration commission and since january 
of this year there have been some changes in the method of 
management 
castillo claramount said the party asked for an investigation of 
the alleged theft of funds if there is evidence it occurred the 
party will ask the assembly to remove the immunity merida enjoys as 
a substitute deputy and will ask the electoral council to revoke 
his candidacy he said 
