by the florida supreme court the nations highest court refused to 
review his case twice 
in the second federal court appeal adams in early 1986 
challenged statements made to the jury by the judge in his state 
court sentencing trial 
under florida law a jury recommends life or death for convicted 
murderers in capital cases the presiding judge is free to follow 
or disregard the recommendation 
in adams case the judge told jurors about that aspect of the 
states capitalsentencing law the final decision as to what 
punishment shall be imposed rests solely upon the judge of this 
court the jury was told 
adams argued that such jury instructions run afoul of a 1985 
supreme court decision in which the justices ruling in a 
mississippi case said a death sentence is invalid if a jury is 
misled about its role in determining whether the defendant actually 
will die 
