<TEXT>
potential liability problems 
surrounding a tree house that extends two feet over public property 
have prompted city officials to give the structure the ax 
its accessible to the public and there is the possibility it 
could entirely or partially fall on somebody passing by or damage 
property said chief building inspector louis kidwell 
the 8by6foot tree house was built by teresa macdonalds 
father a contractor a few months ago as a christmas present for 
her sons james 6 and joey 4 
it features walltowall carpeting a shingled roof and sliding 
plexiglass windows and is a popular place for neighborhood children 
to play 
if i didnt have school id spend every single day up 
there said james macdonald 
my dad said whatever happened to the days of huckleberry 
finn and tom sawyer said teresa macdonald 
she said she understands the citys concern but added that few 
people use the sidewalk on their deadend street 
ive been up there on the windiest days and nothing has 
happened she said wed have to have an earthquake or a 
nuclear war 
the macdonalds have until march 21 to remove the tree house if 
the city doesnt change its mind they will build a foundation for 
it in their back yard and place it there 
