restricting wood burning on highpollution days they have reduced 
carbon monoxide pollution in the metro area by up to 17 percent 
the campaigns purpose was to reduce traffic volume and 
woodsmoke pollution on days when temperature inversions caused 
denvers carbonmonoxide levels to soar 
the project achieved a 9 percent reduction in traffic on 
highpollution days equivalent to three million miles daily and a 
10 percent reduction in carbon monoxide vehicle emissions said 
anne grady spokeswoman for the colorado department of healths air 
pollution control division she said the programs goal was an 8 
percent traffic reduction and a 9 percent reduction in carbon 
monoxide 
carbon monoxide emissions from woodburning fell 7 percent on 
highpollution days during the most recent better air campaign 
said grady and the goal was a 6 percent reduction 
pena said the 7 percent carbon monoxide reduction attributable 
to observance of woodburning bans was more than double last years 
results 
the better air campaign ran from early november until the end of 
january in its previous three years it ran for just 60 days 
the oxygenated fuels program which was launched for the first 
time in january and lasted two months required all service 
stations along the 130mile corridor along the front range between 
colorado springs and fort collins to sell only oxygenated fuels or 
fuels containing at least 15 percent oxygen 
the programs purpose was to provide a gasoline that would burn 
cleaner in car engines and thus contribute less carbon monoxide 
pollution officials said motorists were offered the choice of an 
ethergasoline blend or gasohol which contains ethyl alcohol 
grady said the oxy fuels program was right on target in its goal 
of reducing ambient carbonmonoxide levels by 8 percent to 10 
percent the reduction was in the 8 percent to 95 percent range 
she said 
