<TEXT>
homestake mining co rejected as inadequate 
an unsolicited 188 billion buyout offer from the partnership led 
by t boone pickens on monday and said it wished to remain 
independent 
the board of directors of homestake the nations biggest gold 
producer unanimously rejected the 20 a share buyout offer made 
last month by pickens mesa limited partnership 
homestake stock closed at 1712 a share monday on the new york 
stock exchange unchanged from fridays close 
pickens had labeled the buyout offer a friendly bid and proposed 
a negotiated transaction with homestakes managers 
but homestakes board concluded the offer was inadequate and not 
in the best interests of the stockholders said company officials 
in light of our business prospects we are better off served 
as an independent company said stephanie kushner homestakes 
manager of financial services we are trying to focus on the 
financial future of the company 
were really in a strong position right now with significant 
cash assets and a very strong balance sheet and our management is 
in a better position to put that money to work for the company 
kushner stated 
homestake one of the largest gold producers in the western 
world outside of south africa owns the homestake gold mine in 
south dakota and the mclaughlin mine in northern california the 
company also has a onequarter interest in the round mountain mine 
in nevada 
in addition homestake owns a 425 percent interest in the doe 
run co the largest us producer of lead products and a 48 
percent interest in two mines in western australia 
kushner noted pickens had not made a tender offer to homestake 
shareholders and she was unsure whether he would now pursue a 
hostile takeover in light of the boards rejection 
the offer was pickens second move on a goldmining company in 
six months his 2 billion takeover attempt for new yorkbased 
newmont mining corp was blocked when newmonts biggest 
shareholder consolidated gold fields plc acquired a controlling 
stake in the company to help thwart the hostile bid 
</TEXT>
